<font color="#FF0000">BIG RIFLES</font><br>
<tt>Thu Sep 18 23:07:53 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Guys,<br><br>
You talk about your big guns.  I had the opportunity to watch the awesome cannons play.<br><br>
Scheduled mission to fly with cap support over some navy ship shelling above the DMZ.  I had seen the cruisers firing their 8 inch guns so I felt it would be a boring night.<br><br>
The Gulf was beautiful that night.  A full moon, so bright you could see the ships from angels 30.  Pulled up on posit and saw the New Jersey standing off the coast dead in the water.  Smooth sea, not a ripple.<br><br>
Called on station and then the call went out.  All aircraft firing at posit,, clear all altitudes angels 26 and below.  Hell she looked like she was 10K off the coast.<br><br>
The sea was bright and the beach glowed in the moonlight.  Then the guns went hot.  The big 16inch rifles salvoed.  You could see the gun gas roll out the barrels and light the sea.  The beach glowed from the intensity 10K away.  Waves rolled off her back from the massive recoil traveling out into the gulf and she settled back into the water.  The shells were visible in the dark.  You could see them climb to your altitude going over the top and down the backside with the glow slowly going out.  Seconds later massive explosions could be seen in country.  We let out cheers over the radio.  I swear I could hear those guns.<br><br>
She settled back, the barrels slowly raised and you could feel the coming thunder.  Again the guns spoke with the same display.  I stood over her for hours as she fired into the dawn with deadly accuracy knowing Charlie was getting his ass kicked.<br><br>
Gents you don't know what beauty is until you sit at the top of the parabola.  I'll never forget the sight.<br><br>
SW
